sections.content:
To express patient's privacy policies, we refer to P2U (Purpose-To-Use) language that defines eight main elements;
(1) POLICY, (2) DATA-PROVIDER, (3) PURPOSE, 4) USER, (5) DATA-CONSUMER, (6) DATA-GROUP and (7) DATA and (8) RETENTION [4.]The main particularity of this language is that it supports negotiation. The eight elements are described as follows:
POLICY: The root element of P2U, the policy is created by a provider for a user and with one or more purpose(s) of use . The purpose of data usage constitutes an important parameter in the negotiation process.
